Excellent question! Let me provide a comprehensive analysis of documentation gaps to make this campaign manager truly complete. I'll organize this by priority and audience.

Documentation Gap Analysis
Based on my analysis of the codebase, here's what needs to be documented:

TIER 1: Critical User-Facing Documentation (High Priority)
1. Player's Guide / Getting Started
Status: Missing Priority: CRITICAL Audience: New players Size Estimate: ~2,500 lines, ~150KB

Contents:

Installation and setup
First campaign walkthrough
UI navigation guide (main menu, campaign screen, battle screen, crew management)
Character creation step-by-step
First mission walkthrough
Campaign turn sequence explained
Basic crew tasks (training, trade, explore, find a patron, travel)
Equipment management
Ship management basics
Story track introduction
FAQ for common player questions
Why Critical: Players can't use the application effectively without this. This is player-facing documentation.

